question: Which of the following is the correct chronological order for India's export?
option1: Precious metals> Petroleum products> Pharmaceuticals> Electronic equipments
option2: Petroleum products> Pharmaceuticals> Precious metals> Electronic equipments
option3: Petroleum products> Precious metals> Pharmaceuticals> Electronic equipments
option4: Precious metals> Petroleum products> Electronic equipments> Pharmaceuticals
answer: Precious metals> Petroleum products> Pharmaceuticals> Electronic equipments
explanation: First option is the correct answer
